\f0\b\fs52 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Modular movie revenue split\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 \
This model is 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 economically brilliant
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 . By turning your 24/7 stream into a decentralized, scaling revenue-share platform, you incentivize global artists and musicians to build the stream 
\f3\i \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 for
\f1\i0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  you. You act as the tech infrastructure provider, platform owner, and algorithmic content coordinator, securing your baseline 33.3% share while crowdsourcing production.\
To run this without manual bookkeeping nightmare, you can compute your monthly payout fractions programmatically by mapping out the mathematical scaling formulas and updating your database tracker.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs42 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 1. The Scaling Split Mathematics\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 The revenue share pool is divided into three buckets, totaling a maximum of 100% payout. Your share is fixed, while the content buckets scale dynamically between 0% and 33.333% based on actual utilization over your total loop cycle (e.g., 24 hours / 2,592,000 frames total).\
The algebraic equations for your billing cycle splits look like this:\
$$\\text\{Owner Share\} = 33.333\\%$$ \
$$\\text\{Art Share\} = \\left( \\frac\{\\text\{Frames of Contributed Human Art\}\}\{\\text\{Total Day Cycle Frames\}\} \\right) \\times 33.333\\%$$ \
$$\\text\{Music Share\} = \\left( \\frac\{\\text\{Seconds of Contributed Human Music\}\}\{\\text\{Total Day Cycle Seconds\}\} \\right) \\times 33.333\\%$$ \
$$\\text\{Platform Overhead / Reinvestment\} = 100\\% - (\\text\{Owner\} + \\text\{Art\} + \\text\{Music\})$$ \
\
